altitude.description: The coordinate's altitude in meters, relative to sea level. A value of zero implies that the altitude of the coordinate could not be determined.

accuracy.description: The coordinate's estimated accuracy representing the radius of a circle formed around the reported latitude/longitude pair, for which there is AT LEAST a 68% probability that the true coordinate is contained within (the 'Circular Error Probable'). A value of zero implies that the accuracy of the coordinate could not be determined.

bearing.description: (Currently unsupported.) The bearing is the horizontal direction of travel, in degrees, estimated by the GPS satellites to the device when requesting coordinates, thus this value is different than if calculated from accelerometer and magnetic field measurements.

speed.description: (Currently unsupported.) The current estimated speed of travel over ground, in meters/second.

sensor_specs.description: The location sensor records the device's current GPS coordinates. Depending on the device operating system and device battery level, the source of the data from this sensor may alternate between GPS antennae (high accuracy), cellular tower triangulation (moderate accuracy), WiFi triangulation (poor accuracy), or a combination of these.
